HEADWORD: Tamale
<hw>Ta*ma"le</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>tamal</asp>, <asp>tomale</asp>.]</altsp> <ety>[Amer. Sp.
<ets>tamal</ets>, of Mex. origin.]</ety> <def>A Mexican dish made of
crushed corn (cornmeal) mixed with minced meat, seasoned with red
pepper, dipped in oil, and steamed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tamandu</ent>⟦br⟧
